# Creating an In-Memory Database

Since PostgreSQL has not yet been introduced, products were stored inside a JavaScript array.

At the top of:

```text
backend/src/controllers/productController.js
```

the following was added:

```javascript
const products = [];
```

This array acts as temporary storage while the server is running.

---

# Why the Array Is Outside the Functions

The products array was declared outside the controller functions.

```javascript
const products = [];
```

This ensures that every request shares the same array.

If the array were created inside a controller function, it would be recreated every time a request was received and all previously stored products would be lost.

---

# Storing Products

Inside `createProduct()`, the following line was added:

```javascript
products.push(req.body);
```

`.push()` adds a new item to the end of an array.

Example:

Before:

```javascript
[]
```

After the first POST request:

```javascript
[
    {
        name: "Shampoo",
        price: 850,
        category: "Hair Care"
    }
]
```

After another POST request:

```javascript
[
    {
        name: "Shampoo",
        price: 850,
        category: "Hair Care"
    },
    {
        name: "Conditioner",
        price: 1200,
        category: "Hair Care"
    }
]
```

The array continues growing as new products are added.

