# Returning All Products

Previously, `getAllProducts()` returned a fixed message.

It was updated to:

```javascript
const getAllProducts = (req, res) => {
    res.json(products);
};
```

Instead of returning a hardcoded response, the controller now returns the contents of the products array.

This made the API dynamic for the first time.

---

# Retrieving One Product

A new controller function was added:

```javascript
const getProductById = (req, res) => {
    const id = req.params.id;

    res.json(products[id]);
};
```

This controller returns a single product based on the value contained in the URL.

