# Understanding Route Parameters

A new route was added:

```javascript
router.get("/:id", getProductById);
```

The colon (`:`) indicates a route parameter.

Example:

```text
GET /products/0
```

Inside Express:

```javascript
req.params.id
```

becomes:

```javascript
"0"
```

If the products array contains:

```javascript
[
    { name: "Shampoo" },
    { name: "Conditioner" }
]
```

then:

```javascript
products[0]
```

returns:

```javascript
{
    name: "Shampoo"
}
```

