# req.body vs req.params

A major concept learned during this session was the difference between request bodies and route parameters.

## req.body

Used when the client sends data inside the request.

Example:

```json
{
    "name": "Shampoo",
    "price": 850
}
```

Controller:

```javascript
req.body
```

---

## req.params

Used when the client sends information through the URL.

Example:

```text
GET /products/5
```

Controller:

```javascript
req.params.id
```

Result:

```javascript
"5"
```

