# Key Concepts Learned

* Browsers primarily send GET requests.
* Postman allows testing of all HTTP methods.
* `express.json()` parses incoming JSON requests.
* `req.body` contains data sent by the client.
* `res.json()` sends data back to the client.
* Arrays can be used as temporary storage before introducing a database.
* `.push()` adds new items to an array.
* `req.params` retrieves values from the URL.
* Route parameters allow dynamic endpoints such as `/products/:id`.
* A backend can return dynamic data instead of hardcoded responses by storing and retrieving information from memory.

